# TypeScript File Naming

## Critical Rules

- Use single-word, lowercase names for all files
- One component/feature per file
- Use .tsx for React components
- Use .ts for other TypeScript files
- Use semantic directory structure:
  - components/
  - screens/
  - hooks/
  - utils/

## Examples

<example>
// Good structure
src/
  components/
    button.tsx    // ✓ Single word, lowercase
    card.tsx      // ✓ Focused component
  screens/
    home.tsx      // ✓ Simple screen name
  hooks/
    auth.ts       // ✓ Feature-specific hook
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Bad structure
src/
  Components/                // ✗ PascalCase
    ButtonComponent.tsx      // ✗ Combined words
  pages/
    UserProfilePage.tsx      // ✗ Combined words
    LongComplexFileName.tsx  // ✗ Too verbose
</example>
